Package software.kes.kraftwerk.constraints

Class LocalDateRange

  • java.lang.Object
    • software.kes.kraftwerk.constraints.LocalDateRange
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<java.time.LocalDate>, Constraint<java.time.LocalDate>
    public final class LocalDateRange
extends java.lang.Object
implements Constraint<java.time.LocalDate>, java.lang.Iterable<java.time.LocalDate>
    A range of LocalDates. Like all ranges, it is immutable and its span always includes a minimum of one value.

    Construct using one of the static methods (inclusive(java.time.LocalDate, java.time.LocalDate), exclusive(java.time.LocalDate, java.time.LocalDate)),

    or by using from(java.time.LocalDate): 

     LocalDateRange.from(LocalDate.of(2020, 1, 1)).to(LocalDate.of(2021, 1, 1))      // inclusive upper bound
 LocalDateRange.from(LocalDate.of(2020, 1, 1)).until(LocalDate.of(2021, 1, 1))   // exclusive upper bound

        With the result, you can call to or until with the upper bound to create the LocalDateRange.
